cs.LG, cs.CE, cs.IR, cs.CL, cs.HC 

The paper discusses the development of a personalized linear multiple regression model to predict the grade for a student in a MOOC based on their prior performance or activity in the course. This involves the use of data mining approaches for the analysis of data obtained from MOOCs. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.LG (Machine Learning). Other likely sub-categories include cs.CE (Computational Engineering), cs.IR (Information Retrieval), cs.CL (Computation and Language), and cs.HC (Human-Computer Interaction) as the paper also discusses the identification of key features associated with the study habits and learning behaviors of students.
